  "doc_id": "2244",
  "text": "In this appendix we will prove that the SW-curve with fundamental matter factorizes as in (3.1) if and only if there exist a meromorphic one-form with only simple poles on a hyperelliptic curve, y 2 red = F 2(Nc−n) (x), which has residue −N c at infinity on the upper sheet, residue N c − N f at infinity on the lower sheet, residue 1 at −m i , fulfills (4.6), and, finally, has integral α-and β-periods. [CITATION_1] Note that N c , N f , m i and Λ are thought of as given.",
